Academic activities at the Cape Peninsula University of Technology (CPUT) campuses have been suspended for Tuesday and Wednesday.The decision to suspend classes comes after insourced workers and students at CPUT s Bellville campus held a protest on Monday.It is reported that students and insourced workers are demanding that recently insourced workers receive full benefits.Acting Vice Chancellor Chris Nhlapo has stated that they decided to suspend classes to ensure the safety of all workers and students. After mammoth all day meetings with students and insourced workers, I have consulted with the chair of the council. In the interests of the safety of staff and students, we agreed to suspend all activities, which includes classes and work for tomorrow 25 July and Wednesday 26 July,&#8221; said Nhlapo.Meanwhile, Council will hold an emergency meeting on Wednesday to discuss the issue of insourced workers and their contracts.-TNA Reporter 